{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing","doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/VectorIndex"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"others","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" statement in "},{"code":"VHDL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Refers to all remaining indexes in a vector."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"others","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"s:11VHDLParsing11VectorIndexO6othersyA2CmF","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"others"}],"symbolKind":"case","modules":[{"name":"VHDLParsing"}],"roleHeading":"Case","title":"VectorIndex.others"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/vhdlparsing\/vectorindex\/others"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/VectorIndex\/others","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://VHDLParsing/documentation/VHDLParsing/VectorIndex":{"role":"symbol","title":"VectorIndex","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"VectorIndex","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/VectorIndex","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VectorIndex","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlparsing\/vectorindex","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An index of a vector in "},{"code":"VHDL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This type is designed to represent indexes in an assignment statement for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a vector type. For example, you may have a signal "},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" of type "},{"code":"std_logic_vector(7 downto 0)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want to assign a value to. In "},{"code":"VHDL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", you can do this with the statement "},{"code":"x <= (others => '0');","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This type is designed to represent the "},{"code":"others","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in that statement and other supported values like it, such"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as those found in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x <= (7 => '1', others => '0');"},{"text":". This statement would produce two instances of this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type for the values ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"7"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"others"},{"text":". This type also supports ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VHDL2008"},{"text":" statements that support a range","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of values, e.g. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x <= (7 downto 0 => '1');"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"doc://VHDLParsing/documentation/VHDLParsing":{"title":"VHDLParsing","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/vhdlparsing","role":"collection","abstract":[],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://VHDLParsing/documentation/VHDLParsing/VectorIndex/others":{"type":"topic","title":"VectorIndex.others","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"others"},{"text":" statement in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VHDL"},{"text":". Refers to all remaining indexes in a vector.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"others","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/VectorIndex\/others","url":"\/documentation\/vhdlparsing\/vectorindex\/others","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"}}}